[MESSAGE]Congratulations on your new restaurant!

It seems nice and spacious. However, it also appears that whoever built this quaint "ristorante" forgot to add something - the restrooms! This is something that we have to remedy. First, let's open the _interior panel_ and then _left-click_ on the _Rooms and Textures_ button.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Now, _left-click_ on the _Add Rooms_ button. You will notice that there are three options available: _Female Restroom_, _Male Restroom_, and _Kitchen_. Since this restaurant already has a kitchen, we won't be setting one up here. Suffice to say that most everything you learn here applies to both restrooms and kitchens.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Before we carry on, I want to remind you that context-sensitive help is available for all item placing actions. Simply look at the message bar at the top of the screen to view messages specific to your item placement if you find yourself unable to place an item. Chances are you will find the answer there.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Think about where you are adding a restroom, or a kitchen, for that matter. You can, and should, add male and female restrooms to every restaurant, unless you want to trigger customer complaints about not being able to use restrooms in your establishment!

Let's add a restroom. Ladies first! _Left-click_ on the _Female Restroom_ button. 
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]You will notice that the cursor has changed. Now, to draw the first corner of the room, _left-click_ on the restaurant floor, but _keep the mouse button pressed_!

See the tiny red square? That is the starting corner of your restroom. Now, _drag the mouse_ towards any direction within the restaurant floor. You will notice the square grows in size. If the square is big enough, and not obstructed by any objects or rooms, the square will eventually turn green.

Try it now. _Release_ the _left mouse button_ when the square turns green. If you have any trouble, you can always refer to the context-sensitive help located at the top of the screen.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]And there you go! Your first restroom! Now to make the restroom fully functional, you need to add some items, such as a _door_, some _sink sets_, and the ever-popular _stall_. But before you go and place all these items in your spanking-new restroom, we're going to see how to resize and move a restroom, or any other room.  _Left-click_ on the _Adjust Rooms_ button. You will notice the cursor change.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Now _left-click_ on the restroom floor. You will see the floor start flashing white. You will also see four green squares, one on each corner. You can _resize_ the room or _move_ it somewhere else.

To _resize_ a room, _left-click_ on a green square and _keep the button down_. Then, _drag_ the green square to another location within your restaurant. When you _release_ the button, your room will be resized.

Give it a try, then _left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Good! To _move_ an entire room, _left-click_ on the restroom floor again, then _left-click_ on the white area. Your room will appear to "float", and the white area will turn either green or red, depending on whether you can place the room there or not.

Provided the area remains green, you can move the room to another area in your restaurant. To confirm the move, _left-click_ on the green area.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Great! To delete a room, _left-click_ on the _Delete Rooms_ button. You will notice the cursor change. Then _double-click_ on the restroom floor to delete it.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Excellent! You are really getting the hang of it! Now let's do it for real. Place two restrooms - a male and a female restroom, complete with door, two sink sets and three stalls each.

When you are done, _left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Fantastic! Now we're going to look at the _Item Detail_ interface. First, let's add a table to the restaurant. Second, add a wall light. They can be found under the _Restaurant Lighting & Facilities_ button.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Now, _double-click_ on the table. 
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]The _Item Detail_ interface will show up, displaying the table set name as well as a 3D model. It will also indicate the monthly maintenance cost of the item, as well as its comfort and decoration values, which count towards your restaurant rating.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]See the _arrow_ buttons and the _display bar_ between the arrows? You can use the arrows to view the different options available under _tabletop amenities_, but another, easier way to view items is to _left-click_ the _display bar_. Doing this will show a dropdown list of available amenities. Try it now, and _scroll down_ until you find the _Dining Table Light_ and _left-click_ on it.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]You can see that the interface now shows a preview of the item next to the _left arrow_ button. That means the current lamp is selected.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Now note the other two _arrow_ buttons and _display bar_. Here you can choose whether to _Apply_ the _Dining Table Light_ _on this table only_, _Apply to similar tables_, or _Apply to all tables_. Place this light on all the tables to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Good going! Now all the tables in the restaurant will sport the same light. Now _double-click_ on any wall lamp. The _Item Detail_ interface will appear again, this time indicating relevant information about the lamp. If you want to change the light's illumination radius or intensity, _left-click and drag the slider_ to adjust the settings. Once again, you can use the dropdown or arrows to choose how you want to apply the settings.

When you are done with the light settings, _left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Now I'm going to explain about assigning specific chefs to cook specific recipes. First, open the _recipe menu_ and add the _Spicy Marinated Mozzarella with Oregano and Capers_ recipe to your _Food menu_.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Now, open your _Food menu_, and _highlight_ the _Spicy Marinated Mozzarella with Oregano and Capers_ recipe. Notice the small chef icon? That is the _Assign Chef_ button. _Left-click_ it now. You will see the _Chef & Ingredient Assignments_ interface.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Notice the _display bar_? That's the currently highlighted chef. Right now, you cannot assign anyone else to prepare this recipe, because you only have one chef in this restaurant! If you had more chefs, you could use the _arrow_ buttons that normally appear to the sides of the _display bar_. For now, let's stick with Mario.

To assign young Corleone to cook this recipe, _left-click_ on the _Assign Chef_ checkbox to continue. A checkmark will appear to confirm, which means whenever a customer orders this recipe, Mario Corleone will prepare it, even if there are other chefs around.
[POSITION]572,27
[DIMENSION]228,250

[MESSAGE]Now take a look at the right hand column of the interface. This is the _Stocked Ingredients_ column. You will notice many empty bars, except for one that says "Caper". That means Mario carries a required ingredient for the making of the recipe. If you want the chef to prepare the recipe with the stocked ingredient, then _left-click_ on the _checkbox_ next to the ingredient name. Try it now.
[POSITION]572,27
[DIMENSION]228,250

[MESSAGE]Why assign chefs and stocked ingredients, you ask? Simple! The more a chef dedicates his time and efforts to a recipe, the more experience he gains, and hence the better the recipe will taste! Stocked ingredients also tend to be of better quality, so it means your recipe can only get better with time.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]572,27
[DIMENSION]228,250

[MESSAGE]If you want to reset chef assignments, _left-click_ on the checkmark again to clear it. No chefs will be assigned to that recipe. If you want to reset ingredient assignments, _left-click_ on the _Uncheck All Ingredients_ button.

_Left-click_ on the _OK_ to continue.
[POSITION]572,27
[DIMENSION]228,250

[MESSAGE]Now I'm going to introduce an essential concept in the food and beverage industry - that of sourcing choice ingredients. We all know that to prepare quality recipes, you not only need quality chef skills, but also quality ingredients. During the course of your career as a restaurateur, you will encounter customers that may supply you with ingredient suppliers. These suppliers differ from normal suppliers in that their ingredients are invariably better. So you owe it to yourself to try to obtain these contacts! Every time you see a customers with a large, green arrow above their heads, _left-click_ on the customer and they will tell you not only special ingredient supplier locations, but may also let you in on culinary secrets.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]You can purchase quality ingredients from these suppliers simply by selecting recipes on the _Recipe Menu_ that have the _Special Supplier_ icon on the ingredient list, and _left-clicking_ on that button. The _Special Supplier_ interface will appear and you can make your special ingredient purchases there.
[POSITION]374,318
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]For the next few steps, you will have to open your restaurant first to allow customers in! Don't worry if at this point your restaurant is not completely set-up. Just make sure that you have a few recipes, some staff on board, and a few recipes for your customers to choose from.

Once you have setup the basic necessities of a restaurant, and you have some customers getting ready to eat, _left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue, but remember that you will move on to the next step only if you have finished setting up the restaurant, open it for business, and have customers entering. You may want to minimize the tutorial window for this step.
[POSITION]374,318
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]The last concept I am going to explain to you is about customer satisfaction. There are many ways to gauge your customer satisfaction. First, let's take a look at your satisfaction ratings. To do so, _left-click_ on the _Customer Panel_ button.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Now, _left-click_ on any customer from your customer list. Your new restaurant may not yet have any customers at this point. If you don't have any customers yet, minimize the tutorial window, and strive to attract some customers to your restaurant. When customers start entering, continue with this tutorial by selecting a customer in your customer list.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]_Left-click_ on the _Customer Profile_ button. You will see a detailed breakdown of the selected customer.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Pay special attention to the _Satisfaction_ rating indicator. The more happy faces, the more satisfied the customer is. You can also see the customer's _Quality Expectation_ just above the _Actual Food Quality_ and _Satisfaction_ indicators. A customer's satisfaction is high when the customer's food quality meets or surpasses the customer's expectation. Strive to make the _Actual Food Quality_ rating higher than the customer's expectations, and you'll be fine. If you see a customer with five happy faces, then you can safely say that the customer has discovered culinary nirvana!

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]There are other ways to increase a customer's satisfaction levels in your restaurants. One of these is to lower the menu price. Some customers don't mind paying a premium for quality, but I'm sure nobody will mind it the same quality can be had for cheaper!

Now _left-click_ on the _Customer Complaints_ button. You will see a list of complaints. One of the most effective ways to please customers is to address their individual complaints. Now while it's true that you just can't please everyone, you will see less sour faces if you actually do something about their complaints!

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Another tip I can offer you is to remove recipes from your food menu that your chefs are not good at preparing. This will help your restaurant maintain a consistently high quality of food offered. You can see a summary of the quality of food sold in the Sales report in the Information Center.

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Before I leave you to it, here's a word of advice: the higher the restaurant's customer awareness, the more customers will come to the restaurant. You can view your restaurant's awareness levels and the expected daily customers on the _Restaurant Detail Panel_. 

_Left-click_ on the _Next_ button to continue.
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250

[MESSAGE]Other factors that affect your expected daily customers include the restaurant's location, and the _Restaurant Rating_, which can be viewed in the _Information Center_ interface, under _Reports_.

Aim to please your customers, and your customers will please you with results that will benefit your restaurant, and your entire operation as a whole!
[POSITION]535,15
[DIMENSION]320,250
